1
00:00:03,213 --> 00:00:05,465
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,548 --> 00:00:08,176
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,301 --> 00:00:13,348
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,431 --> 00:00:18,478
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:26,986 --> 00:00:31,241
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,324 --> 00:00:35,370
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,453 --> 00:00:39,666
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,335 --> 00:00:48,258
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,341 --> 00:00:51,553
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,512 --> 00:00:54,806
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,889 --> 00:00:57,600
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,684 --> 00:01:02,480
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,647 --> 00:01:07,860
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:07,944 --> 00:01:11,364
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,447 --> 00:01:17,245
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:29,424 --> 00:01:32,552
I can't believe my diligent son
is looking at a magazine like that!

17
00:01:33,094 --> 00:01:37,265
Light, it's time for dinner...

18
00:01:44,606 --> 00:01:47,233
<i>I'll solve equations
with my right hand...</i>

19
00:01:47,525 --> 00:01:49,193
<i>And write names with my left.</i>

20
00:01:50,903 --> 00:01:53,489
<i>Grab a potato chip. . .And eat it!</i>

21
00:01:54,657 --> 00:01:57,910
<i>The witness to my alibi is L himself.</i>

22
00:01:59,037 --> 00:02:02,040
ENCOUNTER

23
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:05,168
Are you sure, Ryuk?

24
00:02:05,918 --> 00:02:08,379
Yeah. You definitely aren't being followed.

25
00:02:10,381 --> 00:02:13,676
G-Give it to me quickly.
My withdrawal symptoms are...

26
00:02:14,218 --> 00:02:17,597
You're not saying that
just because you want an apple, are you?

27
00:02:17,847 --> 00:02:19,265
Hey, hey!

28
00:02:19,515 --> 00:02:24,687
I flew around, above you a bunch...
up to a radius of a hundred-meters.

29
00:02:24,771 --> 00:02:25,813
I'm sure.

30
00:02:26,064 --> 00:02:27,482
But there was the news report

31
00:02:27,565 --> 00:02:30,610
about Interpol dispatching 1,500 investigators...

32
00:02:30,943 --> 00:02:33,988
You know they were bluffing.
You said it yourself.

33
00:02:34,072 --> 00:02:37,659
If it were real, they would sneak in
and investigate secretly.

34
00:02:39,077 --> 00:02:42,455
All right, Ryuk.
I'll buy you an apple.

35
00:02:42,955 --> 00:02:44,082
All right!

36
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,959
Thank you very much.

37
00:02:47,251 --> 00:02:49,629
Light! Hurry! Hurry!

38
00:02:55,927 --> 00:02:58,638
You know, the way you go around treating
Shinigami...

39
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:05,061
You had me search for cameras...

40
00:03:05,144 --> 00:03:08,481
And made me give up
eating apples in the house.

41
00:03:10,983 --> 00:03:12,443
Eat the core too...

42
00:03:15,530 --> 00:03:20,159
In the end, I'll write your name
into my Death Note and kill ya!

43
00:03:21,661 --> 00:03:22,995
Are you in a position to laugh?

44
00:03:23,371 --> 00:03:26,749
That's right. There's just one thing left
to top everything off.

45
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,962
Ryuzaki...

46
00:03:31,504 --> 00:03:32,505
Yes?

47
00:03:32,630 --> 00:03:36,008
About the purse-snatcher and embezzler's
heart attacks two days ago...

48
00:03:36,509 --> 00:03:40,054
That happened before my family
had any knowledge of it.

49
00:03:40,596 --> 00:03:42,098
Have they been cleared?

50
00:03:42,890 --> 00:03:44,016
I suppose you're right...

51
00:03:44,642 --> 00:03:47,228
Even though Kira can control
the time of death,

52
00:03:47,603 --> 00:03:48,980
I don't think that there's any way

53
00:03:49,063 --> 00:03:51,816
he could set up his victims without
watching that broadcast-!

54
00:03:53,735 --> 00:03:55,319
Your son has come home again.

55
00:04:00,616 --> 00:04:03,703
So, you're gonna ignore me and act like
you're studying again, huh?

56
00:04:06,539 --> 00:04:09,083
<i>I already have an idea of
where all the cameras are.</i>

57
00:04:09,792 --> 00:04:12,336
<i>But I was only able to kill
a purse-snatcher and an embezzler</i>

58
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:14,213
<i>with the potato-chip trick...</i>

59
00:04:14,213 --> 00:04:14,589
SUSPECT: TAYOSHI MURAO

60
00:04:15,423 --> 00:04:18,593
<i>They ended up being minor criminals
compared to those I've killed until now.</i>

61
00:04:19,427 --> 00:04:21,721
- <i>Next</i> on the news- - -
- Are you going to watch I V?

62
00:04:22,930 --> 00:04:25,308
<i>I killed criminals whose names
and faces were broadcast</i>

63
00:04:25,391 --> 00:04:27,477
<i>when I didn't have access
to TV or the Internet.</i>

64
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:29,896
<i>But there still is a chance
that I'll be suspected because</i>

65
00:04:29,979 --> 00:04:34,150
<i>only minor criminals die
when I don't have any information...</i>

66
00:04:34,442 --> 00:04:36,402
<i>- ...an investigation has been opened...
- In other words...</i>

67
00:04:36,486 --> 00:04:41,616
<i>If I also kill minor criminals
being broadcast when I watch TV...</i>

68
00:04:41,741 --> 00:04:43,159
<i>I won't call attention to myself.</i>

69
00:04:44,243 --> 00:04:46,871
<i>Also, when Igo out...</i>

70
00:04:47,413 --> 00:04:49,123
<i>regardless of the severity
of the crime...</i>

71
00:04:49,540 --> 00:04:52,877
<i>I should remember the names
of criminals broadcast...</i>

72
00:04:53,753 --> 00:04:56,255
<i>And kill them at random times...</i>

73
00:04:56,672 --> 00:04:59,801
<i>with the piece of the Death Note
I left in my wallet.</i>

74
00:05:01,886 --> 00:05:04,222
<i>Now, my countermeasures against
the surveillance cameras are perfect.</i>

75
00:05:09,352 --> 00:05:11,687
During these past few days...

76
00:05:11,771 --> 00:05:15,775
I have checked the tapes
and video footage many times.

77
00:05:17,151 --> 00:05:18,611
I've come to a conclusion.

78
00:05:19,612 --> 00:05:23,032
Of the people in the Kitamura and Yagami families,
suspicious activity was observed in...

79
00:05:25,785 --> 00:05:26,869
...l'1O 0H8.

80
00:05:28,996 --> 00:05:30,748
I shall remove the cameras
and wiretaps.

81
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,628
So, in the end the culprit
wasn't here, huh?

82
00:05:36,087 --> 00:05:37,380
Don't lower your guard!

83
00:05:37,463 --> 00:05:39,131
We're going to narrow down
our possibilities once more.

84
00:05:39,215 --> 00:05:40,925
Please don't misunderstand...

85
00:05:42,844 --> 00:05:44,595
I just meant that there wasn't
anyone suspicious

86
00:05:44,679 --> 00:05:47,139
from what I could see
from our footage.

87
00:05:49,725 --> 00:05:52,603
Even if Kira is among them,
he wouldn't give himself away.

88
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:53,980
No.

89
00:05:54,272 --> 00:05:57,859
It means that he was killing criminals
as usual, without showing it.

90
00:05:59,902 --> 00:06:03,531
So are you saying one of them
might be Kira?

91
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:06,117
As I said...

92
00:06:07,034 --> 00:06:08,327
There's a five-percent probability.

93
00:06:12,665 --> 00:06:17,378
<i>Kira was still killing people even while
the surveillance cameras were in place...</i>

94
00:06:18,713 --> 00:06:21,465
<i>I don't know how he does it...</i>

95
00:06:22,508 --> 00:06:25,344
<i>But even if he's able to kill
just by imagining it...</i>

96
00:06:25,845 --> 00:06:28,264
<i>...any normal human being would exhibit
a change in their facial expressions</i>

97
00:06:28,347 --> 00:06:32,018
<i>or behaviors while
committing the murders...</i>

98
00:06:33,477 --> 00:06:34,854
<i>"Kira is not among them,"</i>

99
00:06:35,646 --> 00:06:37,356
<i>is what most people would conclude.</i>

100
00:06:37,857 --> 00:06:41,694
<i>But... If one of them is Kira...</i>

101
00:06:42,737 --> 00:06:45,781
<i>His psychological state
has already reached god-like levels.</i>

102
00:06:46,949 --> 00:06:49,410
<i>Judging sinners without
any change in expression.</i>

103
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:52,330
<i>I want to believe that Kira
doesn't really exist...</i>

104
00:06:52,997 --> 00:06:55,374
<i>that this really is divine judgment.</i>

105
00:06:56,334 --> 00:07:02,048
<i>But, to think that a god would
need a person's face and name to kill is ridiculous.</i>

106
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:05,134
<i>This isn't divine judgment.</i>

107
00:07:06,052 --> 00:07:08,930
<i>I129 the actions of a child/Sh killer
who thinks he is a god.</i>

108
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:10,848
<i>That's all.</i>

109
00:07:12,516 --> 00:07:15,478
<i>The mass murderer known
as Kira definitely exists.</i>

110
00:07:16,187 --> 00:07:17,813
<i>And I will catch him.</i>

111
00:07:18,356 --> 00:07:21,817
<i>But I don't think that Kira will
expose himself</i>

112
00:07:21,901 --> 00:07:24,779
<i>even if I keep
these cameras in place...</i>

113
00:07:26,197 --> 00:07:27,323
<i>What should I do?</i>

114
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,994
<i>It would be best to get him to
tell me himself that he's Kira,</i>

115
00:07:32,078 --> 00:07:34,789
<i>and have him
show me how he kills...</i>

116
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:37,917
<i>But there's no way I can...</i>

117
00:07:45,591 --> 00:07:48,803
Hey, Light. All the cameras
have been removed!

118
00:07:49,011 --> 00:07:50,596
All of them, all of them!

119
00:07:52,014 --> 00:07:54,225
Hey Light, are you listening?

120
00:07:57,019 --> 00:07:58,521
Hey, Light.

121
00:07:59,772 --> 00:08:04,318
Oh, I get it.
The wiretaps might still be here.

122
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:07,738
<i>I'm no longer a suspect.</i>

123
00:08:08,239 --> 00:08:09,281
<i>It went exactly the way I'd planned.</i>

124
00:08:10,616 --> 00:08:13,160
But I will probably continue
to pursue Kira.

125
00:08:13,244 --> 00:08:16,372
<i>And if he's still working
with the Japanese police...</i>

126
00:08:16,998 --> 00:08:20,543
<i>My father will be among
those being used.</i>

127
00:08:21,752 --> 00:08:22,878
<i>If that's the case...</i>

128
00:08:24,463 --> 00:08:26,799
<i>I'll use my father to find
out L's identity so I can...</i>

129
00:08:26,966 --> 00:08:28,092
<i>eliminate him...</i>

130
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:33,472
<i>If I just get rid ofL...</i>

131
00:08:34,765 --> 00:08:37,768
<i>Kira will be one step closer
to becoming the god of the new world.</i>

132
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,315
Light, hurry up.

133
00:08:43,941 --> 00:08:45,026
Do your best!

134
00:08:45,151 --> 00:08:46,986
Good luck, Light!

135
00:08:47,403 --> 00:08:49,238
Really, you're making such
a big fuss over this.

136
00:08:49,655 --> 00:08:50,698
I'll be going now.

137
00:08:55,202 --> 00:08:58,831
It sure feels good, now that we know
that there aren't any wiretaps.

138
00:08:59,165 --> 00:09:00,791
<i>Well, it's nice to know</i>

139
00:09:00,875 --> 00:09:03,335
<i>that one cause of stress
is gone before my test.</i>

140
00:09:04,003 --> 00:09:10,593
2007 TEST CENTER FOR UNIVERSITY ADMISSIONS
TO-OH UNIVERSITY TEST

141
00:09:10,926 --> 00:09:14,263
You there! The test will start
in ten minutes! Hurry up!

142
00:09:15,681 --> 00:09:17,767
I was planning on going in
three minutes before the test

143
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:19,477
because I didn't want to wait around
in the classroom...

144
00:09:20,144 --> 00:09:20,978
I sure got here early.

145
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,064
<i>Talk about confident...</i>

146
00:09:28,778 --> 00:09:29,945
You may begin.

147
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:51,300
You there... Number 162...

148
00:09:51,842 --> 00:09:53,552
Sit in your seat properly!

149
00:10:38,931 --> 00:10:40,850
There's been
a lot of Shinigami...

150
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:43,644
looking real hard into
the human world lately.

151
00:10:43,769 --> 00:10:44,937
What's going on?

152
00:10:45,479 --> 00:10:48,065
It seems that Ryuk has turned
into some human's pet.

153
00:10:48,858 --> 00:10:51,610
W-What in the world is he thinking?

154
00:10:51,986 --> 00:10:55,239
Really. He's a disgrace to
all Shinigami.

155
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:59,201
No, I'm talking about the human
who's keeping him.

156
00:11:00,244 --> 00:11:03,956
Ryuk's probably not a very cute pet.

157
00:11:05,875 --> 00:11:07,251
Well, yeah.

158
00:11:07,334 --> 00:11:11,839
So, what kind of human's keeping him?
Is it a woman? A man?

159
00:11:12,298 --> 00:11:13,299
Who knows?

160
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:15,676
Guess I'll go take a peek as well...

161
00:11:15,968 --> 00:11:16,969
Good grief!

162
00:11:40,534 --> 00:11:44,371
2007 TO-OH UNIVERSITY
ENTRANCE CEREMONY

163
00:11:47,166 --> 00:11:48,876
So you're a college student
now, huh, Light?

164
00:11:49,168 --> 00:11:52,171
I'm kind of...filled with emotion.

165
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:59,094
<i>Now for our freshman address.</i>

166
00:12:00,179 --> 00:12:02,723
Our freshman representative,
Light Yagami.

167
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,391
Yes.

168
00:12:04,683 --> 00:12:05,935
Oh, wow.

169
00:12:06,977 --> 00:12:10,022
And other freshman representative,
Hideki Ryuga.

170
00:12:10,522 --> 00:12:11,774
Oh! Yeah...

171
00:12:12,107 --> 00:12:14,193
Hideki Ryuga, the pop idol?!

172
00:12:14,526 --> 00:12:17,738
Couldn't be... There's no way
he's smart enough to enter To-oh.

173
00:12:17,947 --> 00:12:22,701
Ah... You're right. He doesn't even
look anything like him.

174
00:12:29,083 --> 00:12:31,377
<i>I heard I was going to be giving
the address with someone else, but...</i>

175
00:12:31,835 --> 00:12:33,671
<i>I never thought
it was going to be him.</i>

176
00:12:34,672 --> 00:12:40,177
<i>He's the guy who was sitting weird
behind me on the first day of the Exams.</i>

177
00:12:40,511 --> 00:12:42,930
<i>He completely stood out...
from everyone else.</i>

178
00:12:45,182 --> 00:12:48,060
Life springs renewed
in the breath of Spring...

179
00:12:48,185 --> 00:12:51,230
The person who scored highest on
the test is supposed to do this, right?

180
00:12:51,897 --> 00:12:53,774
That just means that there were
two top scorers this year...

181
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:56,735
I heard they both
scored 100% in all subjects.

182
00:12:56,902 --> 00:12:57,903
Seriously?!

183
00:12:58,070 --> 00:12:59,822
I guess there really are
people like that.

184
00:13:01,407 --> 00:13:03,075
I definitely like the guy on the right!

185
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:06,078
What-?! Kyoko, you're weird!

186
00:13:06,245 --> 00:13:07,454
Most people would choose
the one on the left.

187
00:13:13,252 --> 00:13:15,713
But those two sure are different...

188
00:13:15,796 --> 00:13:16,797
Yeah...

189
00:13:16,964 --> 00:13:20,718
One looks like a brilliant genius
from a sheltered family.

190
00:13:21,093 --> 00:13:22,219
The other...

191
00:13:22,845 --> 00:13:25,431
Life springs renewed
in the breath of Spring...

192
00:13:25,556 --> 00:13:28,434
Seems wild. ..
Or at least very weird...

193
00:13:29,143 --> 00:13:31,270
Is that what people
would call a genius?

194
00:13:32,104 --> 00:13:33,522
He's doing the address...

195
00:13:33,605 --> 00:13:35,482
for the To-oh entrance ceremony
dressed like that.

196
00:13:35,691 --> 00:13:37,776
He is either not taking this seriously
or an idiot.

197
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:40,029
Thank you very much...
Hideki Ryuga.

198
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:53,584
Yagami...

199
00:13:54,168 --> 00:13:58,672
You are the son of Soichiro Yagami,
Detective Superintendent of the NPA.

200
00:13:58,839 --> 00:14:00,341
You have a sense of justice

201
00:14:00,424 --> 00:14:02,384
which rivals that of
your respect for your father.

202
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,136
<i>What is with this guy?</i>

203
00:14:05,512 --> 00:14:08,223
You aim to become an NPA official...

204
00:14:08,682 --> 00:14:12,686
and have helped the police to
solve several cases in the past.

205
00:14:12,936 --> 00:14:15,689
You're now showing great interest
in the Kira case.

206
00:14:17,149 --> 00:14:18,984
I have faith in your sense of
justice and abilities,

207
00:14:19,401 --> 00:14:22,154
and if you swear not to tell anyone,

208
00:14:23,238 --> 00:14:26,825
I'll tell you something very important
concerning the Kira case.

209
00:14:27,826 --> 00:14:29,119
<i>What is this all of a sudden?</i>

210
00:14:29,661 --> 00:14:32,498
<i>Should I just ignore him?</i>

211
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:36,460
<i>But what is this important information
concerning the Kira case?</i>

212
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:39,713
I won't tell anyone. What is it?

213
00:14:44,968 --> 00:14:46,637
I'm L.

214
00:14:51,392 --> 00:14:55,229
<i>I-It couldn't be!
What is he talking about?!</i>

215
00:14:55,854 --> 00:14:57,815
<i>There's no way that
I would say that he's L.</i>

216
00:14:58,482 --> 00:15:01,527
<i>I thought he was weird,
but is he actually insane?</i>

217
00:15:03,237 --> 00:15:04,696
<i>T-This isn't good.</i>

218
00:15:05,239 --> 00:15:08,409
<i>Don't be shocked.
If he really is L...</i>

219
00:15:09,368 --> 00:15:11,954
<i>I have to act naturally,</i>

220
00:15:12,037 --> 00:15:15,416
<i>like how
Soichiro Yagami's son, Light would act.</i>

221
00:15:20,003 --> 00:15:24,174
If you truly are who you say you are,
I respect and admire you.

222
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:25,801
Thank you...

223
00:15:26,218 --> 00:15:28,303
I revealed myself
because I think that

224
00:15:28,387 --> 00:15:31,432
you can be of help in solving
the Kira case.

225
00:15:33,016 --> 00:15:34,059
<i>Light Yagami...</i>

226
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:37,229
<i>The probability that you are Kira
is just under five percent.</i>

227
00:15:37,688 --> 00:15:40,858
<i>But out of everyone we were watching,
I sensed something from you.</i>

228
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:43,235
<i>You're too perfect.</i>

229
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:48,115
<i>And if you're Kira, there's nothing that
could pressure you more than this.</i>

230
00:15:48,824 --> 00:15:53,829
If this guy's really L,
he's something else.

231
00:15:54,204 --> 00:15:57,082
<i>Indeed. . .if he really is L.</i>

232
00:15:57,791 --> 00:16:00,335
<i>No, even if he isn't L...</i>

233
00:16:01,086 --> 00:16:02,254
<i>I...</i>

234
00:16:02,963 --> 00:16:05,966
<i>I can't do anything to him!</i>

235
00:16:08,594 --> 00:16:10,637
<i>If what he's saying is true,</i>

236
00:16:10,846 --> 00:16:13,265
<i>he's probably already shown
his face to my father.</i>

237
00:16:13,932 --> 00:16:17,686
<i>If he dies as soon as he reveals
himself to me,</i>

238
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:19,938
<i>then it would immediately
cast suspicion onto me.</i>

239
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:25,777
<i>And he's using an obvious
alias like "Hideki Ryuga. "</i>

240
00:16:26,737 --> 00:16:29,281
<i>If his name really
isn't Hideki Ryuga</i>

241
00:16:29,573 --> 00:16:32,409
<i>and I try to kill him by writing
his name in the Death Note...</i>

242
00:16:32,409 --> 00:16:35,454
HIDEKI RYUGA

243
00:16:35,454 --> 00:16:35,829
<i>Ryuga, the pop star's face will pop up
in my head whether! want it to or not...</i>

244
00:16:36,413 --> 00:16:37,998
<i>and he may die instead...</i>

245
00:16:38,957 --> 00:16:42,127
<i>But he won't die and
he'll infer that I'm Kira.</i>

246
00:16:43,587 --> 00:16:45,005
<i>Is he really L-?</i>

247
00:16:45,714 --> 00:16:47,966
<i>And does he suspect that I'm Kira?</i>

248
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:52,179
<i>I don't know how much he knows,
but I'm sure he suspects me.</i>

249
00:16:53,305 --> 00:16:56,642
<i>There's no other reason for him to
tell Soichiro Yagami's son that he's L.</i>

250
00:16:58,101 --> 00:17:00,187
<i>Does this mean that
he's still focusing on</i>

251
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:02,314
<i>the people that
Raye Penber was investigating?</i>

252
00:17:03,899 --> 00:17:06,193
<i>But why would L approach
me directly-?</i>

253
00:17:08,153 --> 00:17:11,448
<i>Not now...
It's better to keep my mind blank.</i>

254
00:17:12,324 --> 00:17:13,992
<i>I need to look calm.</i>

255
00:17:14,826 --> 00:17:19,581
<i>He's definitely watching me to
see if I'm rattled or not...</i>

256
00:17:22,584 --> 00:17:25,254
2007 TO-OH UNIVERSITY
ENTRANCE CEREMONY

257
00:17:29,508 --> 00:17:33,387
Light, that was a fun
college entrance ceremony.

258
00:17:38,976 --> 00:17:40,143
Yagami.

259
00:17:40,769 --> 00:17:43,355
Hey, Light... He's calling you.

260
00:17:44,773 --> 00:17:45,899
It was nice to meet you...

261
00:17:46,066 --> 00:17:47,693
No, the pleasure was all mine...

262
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:52,656
What an amazing car...

263
00:17:52,781 --> 00:17:53,865
A limousine?

264
00:17:54,199 --> 00:17:56,243
Well, I'll see you around campus.

265
00:17:56,535 --> 00:17:57,578
Oh, yeah.

266
00:18:00,706 --> 00:18:02,332
Where is that rich kid from?

267
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:05,460
And he's even at the top of the class?
What a jerk.

268
00:18:26,398 --> 00:18:28,191
Welcome home,
To-oh University student!

269
00:18:41,121 --> 00:18:42,581
Damn it! He got me!

270
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:44,124
He "got you". . .?

271
00:18:44,875 --> 00:18:48,462
Damn it, L... I've never been
so humiliated in my life!

272
00:18:49,004 --> 00:18:53,133
Hey, why don't you just do
the Shinigami eye deal with me

273
00:18:53,216 --> 00:18:54,760
and just kill him?

274
00:18:55,719 --> 00:18:58,597
What good would that
do if this is a trap?!

275
00:18:59,264 --> 00:19:03,894
If he's not really L, then that would
be just like telling L that I'm Kira!

276
00:19:04,394 --> 00:19:05,937
S-Sorry...

277
00:19:07,022 --> 00:19:08,982
Shinigami killing people and

278
00:19:09,066 --> 00:19:12,402
humans killing people
aren't the same thing.

279
00:19:13,445 --> 00:19:15,906
I want to kill him,
no matter what it takes,

280
00:19:15,989 --> 00:19:17,699
but if I do,
it'll be traced back to me...

281
00:19:18,075 --> 00:19:21,828
The Death Note can only kill
a person whose name I write in it...

282
00:19:22,204 --> 00:19:24,831
I cannot control someone
to kill someone else.

283
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:28,585
The Death Note is
a pain in the ass!

284
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:31,713
<i>Light is usually calm,
but he's fuming now...</i>

285
00:19:31,963 --> 00:19:33,298
<i>He's pretty annoyed.</i>

286
00:19:33,799 --> 00:19:35,676
At first, I thought that when
I found out his name,

287
00:19:35,759 --> 00:19:38,220
I'd have him get in
an accident or commit suicide.

288
00:19:38,970 --> 00:19:43,934
But it's no good unless
I know a hundred percent that he's L.

289
00:19:44,434 --> 00:19:50,649
No. Even if I do know it's him,
it may be too late.

290
00:19:51,650 --> 00:19:54,986
No matter what the cause of death,
if L dies, I'll cast suspicion on me...

291
00:19:56,446 --> 00:19:57,781
I underestimated him...

292
00:19:59,491 --> 00:20:04,246
I never thought that I would
come up to me and say, "I'm L!"

293
00:20:05,997 --> 00:20:08,333
He just has to tell all
the suspects that he <i>is</i> L.

294
00:20:08,417 --> 00:20:12,045
Even if he's his double...

295
00:20:12,629 --> 00:20:19,177
This is a solid defense as well as
an attack against Kira.

296
00:20:20,178 --> 00:20:22,180
He beat me...
It was a good move...

297
00:20:22,931 --> 00:20:27,644
<i>Ryuga will continue to play dumb and
probably continue to approach me</i>

298
00:20:27,853 --> 00:20:29,771
<i>and manipulate me at the university...</i>

299
00:20:44,911 --> 00:20:45,954
This is great...

300
00:20:46,747 --> 00:20:48,457
There's nothing to worry about.

301
00:20:49,249 --> 00:20:51,877
This proves that they don't have
anything on me...

302
00:20:52,711 --> 00:20:55,547
It's a contest between L and me.

303
00:20:56,381 --> 00:20:57,424
It's a game of wits!

304
00:20:58,592 --> 00:21:01,011
On the surface, we'll be
friendly acquaintances on campus.

305
00:21:01,428 --> 00:21:04,890
In reality, we'll be investigating each other,
"Are you L?" or "Are you Kira?"

306
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:06,850
This will be fun, Ryuga.

307
00:21:07,392 --> 00:21:11,813
If it's friendship you want from me,
I'll gladly accept.

308
00:21:12,564 --> 00:21:14,566
I'll make you trust me...

309
00:21:15,066 --> 00:21:18,612
And once I've pulled everything
out of you, I will kill you...

310
00:21:19,321 --> 00:21:20,906
with my own hands!

311
00:21:23,116 --> 00:21:26,203
TO BE CONTINUED

312
00:21:26,578 --> 00:21:31,500
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

313
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:36,922
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

314
00:21:37,339 --> 00:21:40,509
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

315
00:21:40,592 --> 00:21:45,931
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

316
00:21:46,056 --> 00:21:52,312
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

317
00:21:52,395 --> 00:21:56,900
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

318
00:21:57,692 --> 00:22:02,572
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

319
00:22:02,864 --> 00:22:06,451
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

320
00:22:06,535 --> 00:22:10,038
<i>To accomplish</i>

321
00:22:10,622 --> 00:22:15,252
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

322
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:20,924
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

323
00:22:21,007 --> 00:22:25,971
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

324
00:22:26,596 --> 00:22:31,893
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

325
00:22:36,189 --> 00:22:38,191
PREVIEW

326
00:22:38,191 --> 00:22:39,442
Hideki Ryuga, L...

327
00:22:39,943 --> 00:22:43,864
There's no way that he could
profile me with this tennis game.

328
00:22:43,947 --> 00:22:45,448
He has some other goal in mind.

329
00:22:45,782 --> 00:22:48,326
But even if it is tennis,
I will win!

330
00:22:48,368 --> 00:22:51,204
NEXT EPISODE: DOUBT

